  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Ops. Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Logistics Operations / Warehouse Assistant (Semiconductor Trading Company)</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Perform the assigned logistics works e.g, cargo reception, inspection, manual lifting, pick & pack, space allocation, taping, labelling, sorting, etc by SOP / instruction given.</p></li><li><p>Inbound: to check the accuracy and condition of physical goods against paperwork and to report all exceptions found upon acceptance at warehouse; then follow by Put-Away to designated location.</p></li><li><p>Outbound: build boxes for shipment, to pick & pack by using PDA Barcode Scanner, and labelling of goods, placed packaged items in the correct area.</p></li><li><p>Seek necessary information in our warehouse system when needed.</p></li><li><p>Assist in stock-take to ensure zero discrepancies.</p></li><li><p>Monitoring stock status, i.e. carton boxes, packing tools & materials.</p></li><li><p>To carry out housekeeping of warehouse and to keep work areas tidy at all times.</p></li><li><p>To comply with safety regulations and security measures for warehouse operations.</p></li><li><p>Team player.</p></li><li><p>Not much OT but willing to work OT when required.</p></li><li><p>Any other ad-hoc duties assigned.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Candidate is required manual lifting cartons around 20kg per carton.</p></li><li><p>Experience in PDA Barcode Scanner and Warehouse Management System (WMS), is preferred</p></li><li><p>2 – 3 years’ experience in warehouse operations in the similar industry will be an added advantage.</p></li><li><p>Basic written / verbal English.</p></li><li><p>Attention to detail, follow procedures accurately and carefully</p></li><li><p>Able to express clearly, listen and understand effectively (instruction & feedback)</p></li><li><p>No minimum education required.</p></li><li><p>Candidate who is able to speak Mandarin will be an added advantage as we need to coordinate with the Chinese speaking counterparts.</p></li><li><p>Only Singaporean to apply. No quota.</p></li><li><p>Able to start work with short notice.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Benefits and Others:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Year-end bonus, annual increment, aircon environment, medical insurance, uniform and more.</p></li><li><p>5 days</p></li><li><p>Near Tai Seng MRT</p></li></ul><p><strong>**Only shortlisted candidates will be notified**</strong></p>",
